header.gameNote: MEDIACOM TWO RIVERS SHOOTOUT AT DES MOINES IA

article.headline: Northern Iowa 68, Western Carolina 46
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Eric Coleman scored 17 points on 7-for-9 shooting and Ben Jacobson added 12 as Northern Iowa opened its season with a 68-46 victory over Western Carolina on Sunday night. Northern Iowa, the favorite in the Missouri Valley Conference, shot 54 percent in taking a 37-20 halftime lead and was never threatened in the second half, holding Western Carolina (1-4) to just two baskets in the first 9:44 of the period. Western Carolina shot only 29 percent (7-for-24) in the second half and 36.4 percent for the game. Antonio Russell led the Catamounts with 11 points. They had little to cheer until Charles Bouie leaped to grab a missed shot and slammed in a two-handed dunk with 2:10 left, bringing the team's reserves out of their seats on the bench. The game was the second half of a doubleheader at the recently opened Wells Fargo Arena. Drake beat Detroit 69-61 in the opener, the first basketball game played in the building. Northern Iowa took control with a 25-10 run in the final 10 minutes of the first half. Jacobson scored eight points in that stretch, including a three-point play and a 3-pointer, and reserve Jared Josten hit two 3-pointers. Coleman got free for two layups at the start of the second half and Grant Stout scored inside, stretching the lead to 43-22. With the Panthers cruising, coach Greg McDermott used his reserves liberally the rest of the way.
